worker protection.
Number one is middle-class jobs
should pay

08:50.196 --> 08:55.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a middle-class wage. And, number
two, when
you work extra, you should be
paid extra.

08:55.535 --> 09:00.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the problem we're solving
here, William,
is that over the course of time,
the threshold

09:00.573 --> 09:07.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that differentiated people who
were exempt
employees, that is, exempt from
overtime eligibility,

09:07.514 --> 09:12.886 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
vs. people who are overtime
eligible, it hasn't
kept up with the cost of living.

09:12.919 --> 09:19.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so it has really, really
diminished its
purchasing power. And then,
secondly, in 2004,

09:19.259 --> 09:24.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
