with all those
ominous signs, the eruption was
larger than

41:42.834 --> 41:50.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
anyone predicted. It happened at
8:32 on the
morning of May 18, 1980. An
earthquake caused

41:50.241 --> 41:52.276 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the north face of the mountain
to collapse.

41:52.310 --> 41:57.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BISHOP: After that, it
uncorked an explosion
that was directed horizontally,
and leveled

41:57.648 --> 42:00.685 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the forest to 13 miles out from
the volcano.

42:00.718 --> 42:07.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The eruption
column of volcanic
ash and gas rose 80,000 feet,
while a tsunami

42:07.658 --> 42:16.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of 1,800-degree gas and rock
raced down the
valley at 450 miles an hour, a
so-called pyroclastic

42:16.134 --> 42:17.835 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
flow.

42:17.869 --> 42:21.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BISHOP: Anything biological
that was
remaining after the landslide
would've been

42:21.205 --> 42:27.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
